&lt;p&gt;Become part of a team working on some of the most rewarding, large-scale creative projects to be found in any entertainment medium - all within an inclusive, highly-motivated environment where you can learn and collaborate with some of the most talented people in the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rockstar is on the lookout for a passionate Associate Lead Microsoft Database Engineer who will provide technical leadership, guide database best practices, and drive operational excellence across our global SQL Server environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, in-office position based out of Rockstar’s NYC headquarters in Downtown Manhattan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Rockstar Games Online Services Database Operations Team is a development group, passionate about growing and maintaining the technology platform that powers Rockstar’s online titles and our ability to deliver outstanding player experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Rockstar Database team provides development and operational support for critical platforms and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and mentor a team of SQL Server Database Engineers, fostering collaboration and knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the health, performance, and availability of enterprise-scale SQL Server environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect, implement, and maintain HA/DR solutions using Always On, clustering, and multi-data center best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive automation of routine operational tasks to improve team efficiency and reduce manual intervention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and tune queries, indexes, and server configurations to maximize throughput and minimize latency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with developers to review database code, schema designs, and deployment pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit server health, error logs, and system performance to proactively address potential issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain detailed documentation for standards, processes, and runbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with leadership to plan roadmaps, prioritize initiatives, and align database operations with business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the 24/7 on-call rotation, providing guidance and support for critical incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience with Microsoft SQL Server administration and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience leading or mentoring Database Engineer in enterprise environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert understanding of SQL Server internals, performance tuning, and troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with HA/DR design and multi-data center solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting large-scale, high-concurrency, mission-critical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with database deployment automation and source control integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced T-SQL and query optimization expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of indexing strategies, locking, blocking, and concurrency management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with storage, server, and OS-level performance tuning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyze complex performance issues and drive root cause resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at building automation scripts and tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with other database technologies (MySQL, MongoDB, Redis).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent documentation, communication, and cross-team collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with a focus on scalability, reliability, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

