&lt;p&gt;Rockstar is on the lookout for a passionate Associate Principal Linux Systems Engineer who is skilled at building and supporting Linux environments that are highly redundant and scalable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, in-office position based out of Rockstar’s NYC headquarters in Downtown Manhattan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;24x7 Linux operations of our online games, features, and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on support to the operations of online and development environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and plan infrastructure for upcoming releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on maintenance and administration of Linux based systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform patching and support server migrations as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop standard operating procedures to ensure high availability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine system maintenance when needed to resolve issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support root cause analysis efforts across multiple infrastructure layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a highly available production environment particularly during system maintenances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer monitoring services such as Check_MK, Splunk, Grafana and Graphite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely and creative solutions to difficult problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or related field, IT certifications, or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years’ experience in a Linux environment using related technologies and standards such as DHCP, DNS, LDAP, Kerberos, CIFS/SMB.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth hands-on experience with RHEL or CentOS as well as configuration management experience with either Chef, Puppet or Ansible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience administering systems in a high traffic, multi-system, public facing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience configuring and maintaining Apache servers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience administering one of the following: Elasticsearch, Cassandra, Mongo, Hadoop (Hive, HDFS, Impala, Oozie), MySQL or PostgreSQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess a thorough understanding of network protocols and standards such as TCP/IP, UDP, HTTP/S and SSL/PKI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with major CDN providers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience scripting in one of the following languages: Bash, Python, PHP, or Perl.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with REST API automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLUSES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that these are desirable skills and are not required to apply for the position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting online game development and production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Cisco IOS administration experience for adding removing VLANS and LACP bonds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of PowerShell.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOW TO APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply with a resume and cover letter demonstrating how you meet the skills above. If we would like to move forward with your application, a Rockstar recruiter will reach out to you to explain next steps and guide you through the process.&lt;/p&gt;
