&lt;p&gt;Rockstar Games is on the lookout for a Project Manager who possess a passion for leading execution on cross-functional initiatives. This role is part of the PM / Production organization and provides execution structure, communication discipline, and coordination across teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, permanent and in-office position based in&amp;nbsp;Rockstar’s state-of-the-art game development studio in Edinburgh, Scotland.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT WE DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We partner with team leads, directors, and subject matter experts across IT and Security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We deliver end-to-end project execution for both internal team projects and cross-departmental efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We ensure project requirements are understood across departments, that feasibility is established, and alignment is maintained through delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build collaborative processes with development teams that promote honest, transparent, and frequent communication. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with project planning and execution by collaborating with leadership or subject matter experts on project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle cross-departmental coordination throughout each project’s life cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify and manage risks through escalation and communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify other teams within Rockstar with necessary technical knowledge and responsibilities to cultivate relationships in order to drive a project forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in computer science, information technology, cybersecurity, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience with 3+ years in project management, preferably in the IT or Security domain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of IT / Security principles, technologies, and methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent project management skills, including the ability to plan, organize, and prioritize tasks effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in project management tools and software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, communication (written and verbal), and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment and adapt to changing priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An intrinsic sense of ownership, initiative, and drive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient with Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, PowerPoint, and Excel) and communication tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLUSES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that these are desirable skills and are not required to apply for the position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant certifications (e.g., PMP, CISSP, CISM) are a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
